1
00:00:01,043 --> 00:00:02,753
You are the Weakest Link.

2
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:07,257
This isn't just a game.

3
00:00:09,218 --> 00:00:10,594
There's something else going on.

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:14,056
-We have contestants outside of the games.
-The games continue.

5
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:15,682
DOCTOR: 7his is Satellite Five.

6
00:00:15,891 --> 00:00:18,977
10,000 channels.
All beaming down from here.

7
00:00:19,061 --> 00:00:20,479
My Masters,
they fear the Doctor.

8
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:21,730
Tell me, who are they?

9
00:00:23,232 --> 00:00:24,942
I saw you die!

10
00:00:25,192 --> 00:00:27,152
JACK: That's impossible.
They were destroyed.

11
00:00:27,236 --> 00:00:28,445
Obviously they survived.

12
00:00:28,529 --> 00:00:30,739
We have your associate.

13
00:00:30,822 --> 00:00:34,701
You will obey or she will be exterminated.

14
00:00:34,785 --> 00:00:36,328
-Rose?
-Yes, Doctor.

15
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,121
I'm coming to get you.

16
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:43,460
(DOCTOR WHO THEME MUSIC)

17
00:01:17,953 --> 00:01:21,707
You know the Doctor.
You understand him.

18
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:25,586
-You will predict his actions.
-I don't know!

19
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:30,632
-And even if I did, I wouldn't tell you.
-Predict! Predict! Predict!

20
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:33,885
Tardis detected in flight.

21
00:01:33,969 --> 00:01:37,055
-Launch missiles! Exterminate!
-You can't!

22
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:39,683
The Tardis hasn't got any defences.
You're gonna kill him.

23
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:42,978
You have predicted correctly.

24
00:01:46,732 --> 00:01:48,233
We've got incoming!

25
00:01:57,868 --> 00:02:01,496
The extrapolator's working.
We've got a fully functional force-field.

26
00:02:01,622 --> 00:02:04,666
-Try saying that when you're drunk.
-And for my next trick...

27
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,593
(WHOOSHING)

28
00:02:28,899 --> 00:02:30,776
Rose, get down!

29
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:34,154
-Get down, Rose!
-Exterminate!

30
00:02:41,953 --> 00:02:43,372
You did it.

31
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,753
Feels like I haven't seen
you in years.

32
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,338
I told you I'd come
and get you.

33
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:53,465
-Never doubted it.
-I did. You all right?

34
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:56,301
-Yeah. And you?
-Not bad. Been better.

35
00:02:56,635 --> 00:02:58,345
-Don't I get a hug?
-Oh, come here.

36
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:01,098
I was talking to him.
Welcome home.

37
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,850
Oh! I thought I'd
never see you again.

38
00:03:03,934 --> 00:03:06,228
You were lucky,
that was just a one-shot wonder.

39
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:09,398
Drained the gun of all its power supply.
Now it's just a piece of junk.

40
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:14,486
Patience, my brethren.

41
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:17,030
ROSE: You said they were extinct.
How come they're still alive?

42
00:03:17,114 --> 00:03:19,199
One minute
they're the greatest threat in the universe,

43
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:21,410
the next minute
they vanished out of time and space.

44
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:23,537
They went off to
fight a bigger war.

45
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:26,790
The Time War.

46
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:30,252
-I thought that was just a legend.
-I was there.

47
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:32,421
The war between the Daleks
and the Time Lords,

48
00:03:32,504 --> 00:03:34,756
with the whole of
creation at stake.

49
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:37,884
My people were destroyed
but they took the Daleks with them.

50
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:40,554
I almost thought
it was worth it.

51
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:43,598
And now it turns out
they died for nothing.

52
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:47,853
There's thousands of them now.
We could hardly stop one.

53
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,605
What are we gonna do?

54
00:03:51,106 --> 00:03:54,818
No good stood round here chinwagging.
Human race, you'd gossip all day.

55
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:58,697
The Daleks have got the answers.
Let's go and meet the neighbours.

56
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,781
You can't go out there!

57
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:04,619
-Exterminate!
-Exterminate!

58
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:12,419
Is that it?
Useless. Nul points!

59
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:16,214
It's all right, come on out.
That force-field can hold back anything.

60
00:04:16,298 --> 00:04:17,966
Almost anything.

61
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,427
Yes, but I wasn't going to tell them that.
Thanks.

62
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,762
Sorry.

63
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:29,561
Do you know what they call me in
the ancient legends of the Dalek homeworld?

64
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,313
The Oncoming Storm.

65
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:37,402
You might have removed all your emotions,
but I reckon right down deep in your DNA,

66
00:04:37,486 --> 00:04:41,907
there's one little spark left.
And that's fear.

67
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:47,370
Doesn't it just burn when you face me?

68
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:52,709
So tell me,
how did you survive the Time War?

69
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:56,296
They survived through me.

70
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,605
Rose. Captain.

71
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,275
This is the Emperor of the Daleks.

72
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:20,695
You destroyed us, Doctor.

73
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:24,282
The Dalek race
died in your inferno.

74
00:05:24,366 --> 00:05:28,954
But my ship survived,
falling through time,

75
00:05:29,037 --> 00:05:31,832
crippled but alive.

76
00:05:31,915 --> 00:05:34,125
-I get it...
-Do not interrupt!

77
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:37,712
-Do not interrupt!
-Do not interrupt!

78
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:39,881
I think you're
forgetting something.

79
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:42,968
I'm the Doctor and if there's
one thing I can do, it's talk.

80
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:46,721
I've got five billion languages
and you haven't got one way of stopping me.

81
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:49,432
So if anybody's
gonna shut up, it's you!

82
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:53,478
Okie-doke. So, where were we?

83
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:58,316
We waited here,
in the dark space,

84
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,570
damaged but rebuilding.

85
00:06:02,237 --> 00:06:04,155
Centuries passed

86
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:09,286
and we quietly infiltrated
the systems of Earth,

87
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:12,664
harvesting the waste of humanity.

88
00:06:12,998 --> 00:06:15,500
The prisoners, the refugees,

89
00:06:15,584 --> 00:06:19,379
the dispossessed,
they all came to us.

90
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:23,717
The bodies were filleted,
pulped, sifted.

91
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:27,220
The seed of
the human race is perverted.

92
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:31,892
Only one cell in a billion
was fit to be nurtured.

93
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:35,604
So you created an army of Daleks
out of the dead.

94
00:06:35,687 --> 00:06:38,815
That makes them half human.

95
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:42,193
Those words are blasphemy!

96
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:46,281
-Do not blaspheme!
-Do not blaspheme!

97
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:48,199
Do not blaspheme!

98
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:52,203
Everything human
has been purged.

99
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:54,205
I cultivated

100
00:06:54,289 --> 00:06:57,792
pure and blessed Dalek.

101
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,716
Since when did the Daleks
have a concept of blasphemy?

102
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:09,721
I reached into
the dirt and made new life.

103
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:14,100
I am the God of all Daleks!

104
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:16,603
-Worship him!
-Worship him!

105
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:18,021
Worship him!

106
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:20,065
They're insane.

107
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:25,195
Hiding in silence for hundreds of years,
that's enough to drive anyone mad.

108
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,530
But it's worse than that.

109
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:31,159
Driven mad by your own flesh.

110
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:35,538
The stink of humanity.

111
00:07:39,334 --> 00:07:41,670
You hate your own existence.

112
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:47,926
And that makes them
more deadly than ever.

113
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:53,098
-We're going.
-You may not leave my presence!

114
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:57,143
-Stay where you are!
-Exterminate!

115
00:07:57,352 --> 00:08:01,690
-Exterminate!
-Exterminate!

116
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,734
(ECHOING) Exterminate!
Exterminate!

117
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:08,029
-Worship him!
-Worship him!

118
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:12,575
You will be exterminated!

119
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:18,999
(WHOOSHING)

120
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:25,130
Turn everything up! All transmitters,
full power, wide open, now! Do it!

121
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:26,256
What does this do?

122
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:27,799
Stops the Daleks
from transmatting on board.

123
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:29,342
How did you get on?
Did you contact Earth?

124
00:08:29,426 --> 00:08:31,553
I tried to warn them,
but all they did was suspend our licence

125
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,805
'cause we stopped the programmes.

126
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:36,599
And the planet's just sitting there.
Defenceless.

127
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:40,854
Lynda, what are you still doing on board?
I told you to evacuate everyone!

128
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:43,231
-She wouldn't go.
-I didn't wanna leave you.

129
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:47,444
There weren't enough shuttles anyway
or I wouldn't be here.

130
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,779
We've got about 100 people
stranded on Floor Zero.

131
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:54,242
Listen, my name's Rodrick.
I won the game, where's my money?

132
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:57,454
Is anyone listening?
Where's my money?

133
00:08:57,787 --> 00:08:59,831
Oh, my God.
The Fleet is moving.

134
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:01,291
They're on their way!

135
00:09:06,921 --> 00:09:09,799
Purify the Earth with fire.

136
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:14,804
The planet will become my temple
and we shall rise.

137
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:20,185
This will be our paradise!

138
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:30,445
Dalek plan, big mistake,
"cause what've they left me with?

139
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:33,323
Anyone? Anyone?
Come on, it's obvious!

140
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:36,284
A great big transmitter.
This station!

141
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,579
If I can change the signal,
fold it back, sequence it? Anyone?

142
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:42,082
-You've got to be kidding.
-Give the man a medal!

143
00:09:42,165 --> 00:09:44,375
-A Delta Wave?
-A Delta Wave!

144
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:47,170
-What's a Delta Wave?
-A wave of Van Cassadyne energy.

145
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:48,630
It fries your brain.

146
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:51,299
Stand in the way of a Delta Wave
and your head gets barbecued.

147
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:54,719
And this place can transmit a massive wave.
Wipe out the Daleks!

148
00:09:54,803 --> 00:09:56,638
Get started and do it, then!

149
00:09:56,721 --> 00:09:59,599
Trouble is, wave this size,
building this big, brain as clever as mine,

150
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:01,476
should take about three days.

151
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:04,813
-How long till the Fleet arrive?
-22 minutes.

152
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:20,870
JACK: We've now got a force-field,
so they can't blast us out of the sky.

153
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:23,456
But that doesn't stop
the Daleks from physically invading.

154
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:24,666
Do they know about
the Delta Wave?

155
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:27,085
They'll have worked
it out at the same time.

156
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:29,129
So, they want to stop the Doctor.

157
00:10:29,212 --> 00:10:31,214
That means they've got to get
to this level, 500.

158
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:36,344
Now, I can concentrate the extrapolator
on the top six levels, 500 to 495.

159
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:40,723
So they'll penetrate the station below that
at level 494 and fight their way up.

160
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:42,058
-Who are they fighting?
-Us.

161
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:43,643
What are we fighting with?

162
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:47,230
The guards had guns with bastic bullets,
that's enough to blow a Dalek wide open.

163
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:48,857
There's five of us.

164
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:52,068
Rose, you can help me.
I need all these wires stripping bare.

165
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:54,779
-Right, now there's four of us.
-Then let's move it!

166
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:57,657
Into the lift,
isolate the lift controls.

167
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:05,540
I just wanna say...thanks,
I suppose.

168
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:08,918
-And I'll do my best.
-Me, too.

169
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,310
It's been fun.

170
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:30,190
-But I guess this is goodbye.
-Don't talk like that.

171
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:33,026
The Doctor's gonna do it,
you just watch him.

172
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:34,402
Rose.

173
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,365
You are worth fighting for.

174
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:46,581
Wish I'd never
met you, Doctor.

175
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:49,876
I was much better
off as a coward.

176
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:57,342
See you in hell.

177
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:04,474
He's gonna be all right,
isn't he?

178
00:12:09,771 --> 00:12:11,272
(PEOPLE ARGUING)

179
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:19,906
One last time!
Any more volunteers?

180
00:12:24,494 --> 00:12:27,997
There's an army about
to invade this station.

181
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:30,959
I need every last
citizen to mount a defence.

182
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:34,504
Don't listen to him!
There aren't any Daleks.

183
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:37,257
They disappeared
thousands of years ago.

184
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:42,136
Thanks.
As for the rest of you,

185
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:46,808
the Daleks will enter the station at Floor 494,
and as far as I can tell,

186
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:50,937
they'll head up, not down.
But that's not a promise.

187
00:12:51,813 --> 00:12:54,107
So here's a few
words of advice.

188
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:57,026
Keep quiet.

189
00:12:57,443 --> 00:13:01,239
And if you hear fighting up above,
if you hear us dying...

190
00:13:03,116 --> 00:13:06,160
then tell me that
the Daleks aren't real.

191
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,750
Don't make a sound.

192
00:13:14,002 --> 00:13:15,336
Let's go.

193
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:31,769
Suppose...

194
00:13:36,024 --> 00:13:38,192
-What?
-Nothing.

195
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:42,947
-You said suppose.
-No, I was just thinking.

196
00:13:43,031 --> 00:13:47,201
I mean, obviously you can't,
but you've got a time machine.

197
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:50,204
Why can't you just go back to last week
and warn them?

198
00:13:50,288 --> 00:13:53,583
Soon as the Tardis lands, in that second,
I become part of events.

199
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:54,917
Stuck in the timeline.

200
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:57,545
Yeah, I thought it'd
be something like that.

201
00:13:59,130 --> 00:14:04,344
There's another thing the Tardis could do.
It could take us away. We could leave.

202
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:09,474
Let history take its course.
We go to Marbella in 1989.

203
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:13,144
-Yeah, but you'd never do that.
-No, but you could ask.

204
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:19,275
-Never even occurred to you, did it?
-Well, I'm just too good.

205
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:22,945
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

206
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:26,741
The Delta Wave's started building.
How long does it need?

207
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:37,335
Is that bad?

208
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:39,921
Okay, it's bad. How bad is it?

209
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:45,343
Rose Tyler, you're a genius!
We can do it!

210
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:48,805
If I use the Tardis to cross
my own timeline... Yes!

211
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:57,772
Hold that down
and keep position.

212
00:14:57,855 --> 00:14:59,315
-What's it do?
-Cancels the buffers.

213
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,526
If I'm very clever,
and I'm more than clever, I'm brilliant,

214
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:04,112
I might just save the world.
Or rip it apart.

215
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:05,613
-I'd go for the first one.
-Me, too.

216
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:09,075
Now, I've just got to go and power up
the Game Station. Hold on!

217
00:15:33,224 --> 00:15:37,770
Doctor, what are you doing?
Can I take my hand off? It's moving.

218
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:43,818
Doctor, let me out!

219
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:46,320
Let me out!

220
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:48,406
Doctor, what have you done?

221
00:16:06,883 --> 00:16:09,093
This is Emergency Program One.

222
00:16:09,469 --> 00:16:11,846
Rose, now listen,
this is important.

223
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:15,683
If this message is activated
then it can only mean one thing.

224
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,686
We must be in danger.
And I mean fatal.

225
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:22,106
I'm dead or about to die any second
with no chance of escape.

226
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:24,484
-No!
-And that's okay. Hope it's a good death.

227
00:16:24,609 --> 00:16:27,487
But I promised to look after you
and that's what I'm doing.

228
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:30,364
-The Tardis is taking you home.
-I won't let you!

229
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:32,742
And I bet you're fussing and moaning now.
Typical!

230
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:35,119
But hold on and
Just listen a bit more.

231
00:16:35,203 --> 00:16:38,956
The Tardis can never return for me.
Emergency Program One means

232
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:42,668
I'm facing an enemy that should never
get their hands on this machine.

233
00:16:42,752 --> 00:16:46,422
So this is what you should do,
let the Tardis die.

234
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:51,552
Just let this old box gather dust.
No one can open it, no one will even notice it.

235
00:16:51,969 --> 00:16:55,556
Let it become a strange little thing
standing on a street corner.

236
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:59,101
And over the years the world will move on
and the box will be buried.

237
00:16:59,227 --> 00:17:01,812
And if you want to remember me,
then you can do one thing.

238
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:04,232
That's all. One thing.

239
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,778
Have a good life.

240
00:17:11,614 --> 00:17:15,701
Do that for me, Rose.
Have a fantastic life.

241
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:25,461
You can't do this to me.
You can't.

242
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:28,381
Take me back! Take me back!

243
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:33,719
No!

244
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:53,030
Come on, fly. How do you fly?

245
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:56,367
Come on, help me!

246
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,177
I knew it!

247
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:18,222
I was all the way down Clifton Parade
and I heard the engines.

248
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:21,767
I thought, "There's only one thing
that makes a noise like that.”

249
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:24,520
What is it?

250
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:34,071
Rose, I've called up
the internal laser codes.

251
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:37,617
There should be a different number on
every screen. Can you read them out to me?

252
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:40,244
-She's not here.
-Of all the times to take a leak!

253
00:18:40,328 --> 00:18:42,330
When she gets back,
tell her to read me the codes.

254
00:18:42,413 --> 00:18:45,833
-She's not coming back.
-What do you mean? Where did she go?

255
00:18:46,042 --> 00:18:49,253
-Just get on with your work.
-You took her home, didn't you?

256
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:50,713
Yeah.

257
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:54,425
The Delta Wave.
Is it ever gonna be ready?

258
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:57,845
(DALEK EMPEROR)
Tell him the truth, Doctor.

259
00:18:58,179 --> 00:19:02,266
There is every
possibility the Delta Wave

260
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:07,605
could be complete
but no possibility of refining it.

261
00:19:07,897 --> 00:19:13,069
The Delta Wave must kill
every living thing in its path,

262
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:18,366
with no distinction
between human and Dalek.

263
00:19:18,449 --> 00:19:23,704
All things will die.
By your hand.

264
00:19:24,914 --> 00:19:29,085
Doctor, the range of this transmitter
covers the entire Earth.

265
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:33,673
DALEK EMPEROR: You would destroy
Daleks and humans together.

266
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:37,927
If I am God,

267
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,846
the creator of all things,

268
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:44,767
then what does
that make you, Doctor?

269
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,644
There are colonies out there.

270
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:49,063
The human race would survive in
some shape or form.

271
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,565
But you're the only
Daleks in existence.

272
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:54,527
The whole universe is in danger
if I let you live.

273
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:59,323
Do you see, Jack?

274
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:02,493
That's the decision I've got to make
for every living thing.

275
00:20:03,703 --> 00:20:05,996
Die as a human or
live as a Dalek.

276
00:20:07,498 --> 00:20:12,002
-What would you do?
-You sent her home. She's safe.

277
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:16,298
-Keep working.
-But he will exterminate you!

278
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:19,051
Never doubted him, never will.

279
00:20:19,427 --> 00:20:21,887
Now, you tell me,
God of all Daleks,

280
00:20:21,971 --> 00:20:26,100
"cause there's one thing I never worked out.
The words, "Bad Wolf",

281
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:29,895
spread across time and space,
everywhere, drawing me in.

282
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:33,691
-How did you manage that?
- I did nothing.

283
00:20:33,858 --> 00:20:36,610
Come on, there's no secrets now,
Your Worship.

284
00:20:36,694 --> 00:20:40,448
They are not part of my design.

285
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:45,870
This is the truth of God.

286
00:20:52,543 --> 00:20:54,378
JACKIE: And it's gone
upmarket, this place.

287
00:20:54,462 --> 00:20:56,505
They're doing little tubs
of coleslaw now.

288
00:20:56,589 --> 00:21:00,092
It's not very nice.
It tastes a bit sort of clinical.

289
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,512
Have you tried that new pizza place
on Minto Road?

290
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:05,806
-What's it selling?
-Pizza.

291
00:21:05,931 --> 00:21:09,560
-That's nice. Do they deliver?
-Yeah.

292
00:21:11,437 --> 00:21:13,898
Oh, Rose, have something to eat.

293
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:18,903
200,000 years in the future he's dying
and there's nothing I can do.

294
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:22,323
Like you said,
200,000 years, it's way off.

295
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,450
But it's not, it's now.

296
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:28,871
That fight is happening right now.
And he's fighting for us!

297
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:32,124
For the whole planet!
And I'm just sitting here eating chips!

298
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:35,294
Listen to me.
God knows I've hated that man,

299
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:38,339
but right now I love him
and do you know why?

300
00:21:39,632 --> 00:21:42,676
'Cause he did the right thing.
He sent you back to me.

301
00:21:44,220 --> 00:21:48,516
What do I do every day, Mum?
What do I do?

302
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:53,020
Get up, catch the bus,
go to work, come back home,

303
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:55,523
eat chips and go to bed,
is that it?

304
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:56,690
That's what the rest
of us do.

305
00:21:56,774 --> 00:21:58,776
-I can't.
-Why, 'cause you're better than us?

306
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:00,861
No, I didn't mean that!

307
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:06,659
But it was...

308
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:10,788
It was a better life.

309
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:14,208
I don't mean all
the traveling and...

310
00:22:15,626 --> 00:22:19,505
seeing aliens and spaceships
and things, that don't matter.

311
00:22:20,089 --> 00:22:23,759
The Doctor showed me
a better way of living your life.

312
00:22:25,594 --> 00:22:27,805
You know he showed you, too.

313
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:33,102
That you don't just give up.
You don't just let things happen.

314
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:36,814
You make a stand. You say no.

315
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:40,276
You have the guts to do what's right
when everyone else just runs away!

316
00:22:40,401 --> 00:22:42,278
And I just can't...

317
00:22:45,823 --> 00:22:47,700
Right, Lynda,
you are my eyes and ears.

318
00:22:47,783 --> 00:22:51,078
When the Daleks get in, you can follow them
on that screen and report it to me.

319
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:52,621
-Understood.
-They'll detect you.

320
00:22:52,746 --> 00:22:55,165
The door is made of hydra combination,
it should keep them out.

321
00:22:55,291 --> 00:22:57,126
-Should?
-It's the best I can do.

322
00:22:57,209 --> 00:22:58,544
How long till the Fleet arrives?

323
00:22:58,669 --> 00:23:00,296
PROGRAMMER: They accelerated.

324
00:23:05,009 --> 00:23:08,387
This is it!
Ladies and gentlemen, we are at war.

325
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:45,257
You can't spend the rest of your life
thinking about the Doctor.

326
00:23:45,466 --> 00:23:49,428
-But how do I forget him?
-You've got to start living your own life.

327
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:52,181
A proper life.
Like the kind he's never had.

328
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:54,850
The sort of life that you
could have with me.

329
00:24:17,957 --> 00:24:20,960
Over here,
it's over here as well!

330
00:24:21,085 --> 00:24:24,630
That's been there for years.
It's just a phrase, it's just words!

331
00:24:24,922 --> 00:24:27,967
I thought it was a warning.
Maybe it's the opposite.

332
00:24:28,050 --> 00:24:30,135
Maybe it's a message.

333
00:24:30,219 --> 00:24:33,722
The same words written down now
and 200,000 years in the future.

334
00:24:33,806 --> 00:24:37,935
It's a link between me and the Doctor.
Bad Wolf here, Bad Wolf there.

335
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:39,853
Yeah, but if it's a message,
what's it saying?

336
00:24:39,979 --> 00:24:43,607
It's telling me I can get back.
The least I can do is help him escape!

337
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:50,322
Stand your ground, everyone.
Follow my commands. And good luck.

338
00:24:53,158 --> 00:24:56,620
You were right.
They're forcing the air lock on 494.

339
00:25:14,930 --> 00:25:18,559
All the Tardis needs to do is
make a return trip. Just reverse.

340
00:25:18,642 --> 00:25:20,227
Yeah, but we still can't do it.

341
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:22,312
The Doctor always said
the Tardis was telepathic.

342
00:25:22,396 --> 00:25:24,440
This thing is alive, it can listen.

343
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:27,693
-It's not listening now, is it?
-We need to get inside it.

344
00:25:27,860 --> 00:25:31,655
Last time I saw you, with the Slitheen,
this middle bit opened.

345
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:32,990
And there was this light

346
00:25:33,115 --> 00:25:35,159
and the Doctor said
it was the heart of the Tardis.

347
00:25:35,242 --> 00:25:39,204
If we can open it, I can make contact.
I can tell it what to do.

348
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:42,708
Rose, if you go back,
you're gonna die.

349
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:44,626
That's a risk I've got to take.

350
00:25:46,503 --> 00:25:48,172
'Cause there's
nothing left for me here.

351
00:25:48,255 --> 00:25:50,007
-Nothing?
-No.

352
00:25:51,842 --> 00:25:55,512
Okay, if that's what you think,
let's get this thing open.

353
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:13,739
JACK: Okay, activate internal lasers.
Slice them up.

354
00:26:14,865 --> 00:26:17,993
Defences have gone offline.
The Daleks have overridden the lot.

355
00:26:38,514 --> 00:26:42,768
You lied to me!
The bullets don't work!

356
00:27:01,662 --> 00:27:03,122
Faster!

357
00:27:08,961 --> 00:27:10,212
Come on!

358
00:27:11,380 --> 00:27:13,006
It's not moving!

359
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,649
Advance guard
have made it to 495.

360
00:27:30,774 --> 00:27:35,195
-Jack, how are we doing?
-495 should be good. I like 495.

361
00:27:37,156 --> 00:27:40,242
Identify yourself!

362
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:42,953
You are the Weakest Link.
Goodbye!

363
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:47,040
Yes!

364
00:27:48,417 --> 00:27:50,043
You are the Weakest Link...

365
00:27:53,005 --> 00:27:54,882
(WARPED VOICE) Goodbye.

366
00:27:54,965 --> 00:27:58,177
Proceed to next level

367
00:27:59,970 --> 00:28:04,224
They're flying up the ventilation shafts.
No, wait a minute.

368
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:07,311
Oh, my God. Why are they doing that?
They're going down.

369
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:19,698
Exterminate! Exterminate...

370
00:28:21,325 --> 00:28:22,910
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

371
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:25,787
Exterminate! Exterminate!

372
00:28:27,748 --> 00:28:30,667
You can't! You don't exist!

373
00:28:31,418 --> 00:28:36,256
It's not fair! I won the game!
I should be rich!

374
00:28:36,340 --> 00:28:40,093
-I'm a winner! You can't do this to me!
-Exterminate!

375
00:28:40,344 --> 00:28:42,804
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

376
00:28:52,606 --> 00:28:55,609
Floor Zero.
They killed them all.

377
00:28:58,487 --> 00:29:00,697
It was never gonna work, sweetheart.

378
00:29:00,781 --> 00:29:04,409
And the Doctor knew that.
He just wanted you to be safe.

379
00:29:04,493 --> 00:29:08,622
-I can't give up.
-Lock the door. Walk away.

380
00:29:09,081 --> 00:29:12,042
-Dad wouldn't give up.
-He's not here, is he?

381
00:29:13,835 --> 00:29:17,381
-And even if he was, he'd say the same.
-No, he wouldn't.

382
00:29:18,674 --> 00:29:20,634
He'd tell me to try anything.

383
00:29:21,343 --> 00:29:25,180
If I could save the Doctor's life, try anything.

384
00:29:25,264 --> 00:29:29,559
-We're never gonna know.
-Well, I know. 'Cause I met him.

385
00:29:31,687 --> 00:29:34,982
-I met Dad.
-Don't be ridiculous.

386
00:29:36,525 --> 00:29:39,736
The Doctor took me back in time
and I met Dad.

387
00:29:39,820 --> 00:29:41,029
Don't say that.

388
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:45,617
You remember when Dad died,
there was someone with him?

389
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:51,164
A girl, a blonde girl.
She held his hand.

390
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:59,298
You saw her from a distance,
Mum, you saw her.

391
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:03,677
Think about it.
That was me. You saw me.

392
00:30:03,885 --> 00:30:05,679
-Stop it!
-That's how good the Doctor...

393
00:30:05,846 --> 00:30:08,140
Stop it! Just stop it!

394
00:30:25,032 --> 00:30:28,869
-Lynda, what's happening on Earth?
-The Fleet's descending.

395
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:32,748
They're bombing whole continents.

396
00:30:32,914 --> 00:30:37,544
Europa, Pacifica,
the New American Alliance.

397
00:30:39,379 --> 00:30:43,508
Australasia's just, er...gone.

398
00:30:44,009 --> 00:30:46,261
This is perfection.

399
00:30:46,345 --> 00:30:50,515
I have created heaven on Earth.

400
00:30:51,808 --> 00:30:54,811
Floor 499, we're the last defence.

401
00:30:54,936 --> 00:30:58,565
The bullets should work if you concentrate
them on the Daleks' eye stalk.

402
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:00,359
I've got the force-field at maximum,

403
00:31:00,442 --> 00:31:03,403
so Dalek firepower
should be at its weakest.

404
00:31:04,404 --> 00:31:06,948
I'm only here 'cause of you.

405
00:31:07,074 --> 00:31:09,618
I joined the Program
"cause you were on it.

406
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:12,037
Am I supposed to say,
"When this is all over,

407
00:31:12,162 --> 00:31:14,414
"if we're still alive,
maybe we could go for a drink?"

408
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:17,167
-That'd be nice.
-Yeah, well, tough.

409
00:31:25,842 --> 00:31:28,387
There's gotta be
something else we can do.

410
00:31:28,762 --> 00:31:32,599
Mum was right. Maybe we should
just lock the door and walk away.

411
00:31:32,724 --> 00:31:34,101
I'm not having that.

412
00:31:34,184 --> 00:31:37,604
I'm not having you
just give up now, no way.

413
00:31:38,814 --> 00:31:41,691
We just need something
stronger than my car.

414
00:31:42,567 --> 00:31:44,903
Something bigger,
something like that.

415
00:31:57,666 --> 00:32:01,002
Right, you've only got this until 6:00,
so get on with it.

416
00:32:01,086 --> 00:32:04,339
-Mum, where the hell did you get that from?
-Rodrigo. He owes me a favour.

417
00:32:04,423 --> 00:32:07,426
Never mind why. But you were right
about your dad, sweetheart.

418
00:32:07,801 --> 00:32:11,763
He was full of mad ideas
and it's exactly what he would have done.

419
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:15,058
Now, get on with it
before I change my mind.

420
00:32:26,695 --> 00:32:28,488
Open fire!

421
00:32:51,595 --> 00:32:53,430
It's not working!

422
00:32:53,513 --> 00:32:57,476
Concentrate your fire.
Eyestalk 2:00!

423
00:33:04,858 --> 00:33:08,987
Eye vision is impaired!
I cannot see!

424
00:33:09,696 --> 00:33:11,198
We did it!

425
00:33:14,201 --> 00:33:17,078
No. No!

426
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:23,710
I've got a problem.

427
00:33:26,421 --> 00:33:29,341
DALEK: Human female detected.

428
00:33:35,263 --> 00:33:37,557
-They've found me.
-You'll be all right, Lynda.

429
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:40,143
That side of the station's
reinforced against meteors.

430
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:41,895
Hope so.

431
00:33:41,978 --> 00:33:44,481
You know what they say
about Earth workmanship.

432
00:34:40,537 --> 00:34:42,372
Last man standing!

433
00:34:42,455 --> 00:34:46,918
For God's sake, Doctor,
finish that thing and kill them!

434
00:34:47,419 --> 00:34:52,257
Finish that thing
and kill mankind.

435
00:35:08,356 --> 00:35:11,818
-Keep going!
-Put your foot down!

436
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:18,033
-Faster!
-Give it some more, Mickey!

437
00:35:21,369 --> 00:35:22,829
Keep going!

438
00:35:24,331 --> 00:35:26,041
Come on! Come on!

439
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,836
-Keep going!
-Give it some more!

440
00:35:44,684 --> 00:35:45,935
Rose!

441
00:35:49,731 --> 00:35:51,816
(WHOOSHING)

442
00:36:06,748 --> 00:36:09,376
Doctor! You've got
20 seconds maximum.

443
00:36:46,496 --> 00:36:50,375
-Exterminate!
-I kind of figured that.

444
00:36:57,132 --> 00:36:58,675
It's ready!

445
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:15,275
You really wanna
think about this.

446
00:37:15,608 --> 00:37:19,696
'Cause if I activate the signal,
every living creature dies.

447
00:37:19,779 --> 00:37:22,240
I am immortal

448
00:37:22,907 --> 00:37:24,117
Do you wanna put that
to the test?

449
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:28,329
I want to see you
become like me.

450
00:37:28,830 --> 00:37:34,043
Hail the Doctor,
the Great Exterminator.

451
00:37:34,169 --> 00:37:37,756
-I'll do it!
-Then prove yourself, Doctor!

452
00:37:37,964 --> 00:37:41,593
What are you?
Coward or killer?

453
00:37:52,687 --> 00:37:54,355
Coward.

454
00:37:54,481 --> 00:37:55,982
Any day.

455
00:37:56,065 --> 00:38:01,279
Mankind will be harvested
because of your weakness.

456
00:38:02,322 --> 00:38:06,743
And what about me?
Am I becoming one of your angels?

457
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:09,370
You are the heathen.

458
00:38:09,454 --> 00:38:13,583
You will be exterminated.

459
00:38:14,501 --> 00:38:16,169
Maybe it's time.

460
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:24,135
(WHOOSHING)

461
00:38:26,513 --> 00:38:29,766
Alert! Tardis materialising!

462
00:38:30,225 --> 00:38:32,477
You will not escape!

463
00:38:45,323 --> 00:38:48,201
-What have you done?
-I looked into the Tardis.

464
00:38:49,577 --> 00:38:51,412
And the Tardis looked into me.

465
00:38:51,496 --> 00:38:53,748
You looked into the time vortex.

466
00:38:53,873 --> 00:38:55,875
Rose, no one's meant to see that.

467
00:38:56,084 --> 00:38:59,087
This is the Abomination!

468
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:01,047
Exterminate!

469
00:39:07,387 --> 00:39:11,391
I am the Bad Wolf.
I create myself.

470
00:39:14,519 --> 00:39:16,271
I take the words...

471
00:39:18,273 --> 00:39:22,110
I scatter them
in time and space.

472
00:39:24,612 --> 00:39:26,990
A message to lead myself here.

473
00:39:27,699 --> 00:39:31,870
Rose, you've got to stop this!
You've got to stop this now!

474
00:39:34,038 --> 00:39:38,209
You've got the entire vortex running
through your head. You're gonna burn!

475
00:39:39,168 --> 00:39:40,879
I want you safe.

476
00:39:42,255 --> 00:39:43,590
My Doctor.

477
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:47,176
Protected from the false god.

478
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:51,764
You cannot hurt me!
I am immortal!

479
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:54,684
You are tiny.

480
00:39:55,643 --> 00:39:58,563
I can see the whole
of time and space.

481
00:39:58,688 --> 00:40:02,692
Every single atom of your existence
and I divide them.

482
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:11,492
Everything must come to dust.

483
00:40:14,871 --> 00:40:18,416
All things. Everything dies.

484
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:30,595
-The Time War ends.
-I will not die!

485
00:40:32,180 --> 00:40:35,934
I cannot die!

486
00:40:53,284 --> 00:40:55,370
Rose, you've done it, now stop.

487
00:40:56,704 --> 00:40:58,206
Just let go!

488
00:40:59,624 --> 00:41:01,668
How can I let go of this?

489
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:04,671
I bring life.

490
00:41:06,506 --> 00:41:08,216
But this is wrong!

491
00:41:08,675 --> 00:41:11,803
-You can't control life and death!
-But I can.

492
00:41:13,721 --> 00:41:18,518
The sun and the moon,
the day and night.

493
00:41:20,186 --> 00:41:21,854
But why do they hurt?

494
00:41:22,063 --> 00:41:24,774
The power's gonna kill you.
And it's my fault!

495
00:41:25,817 --> 00:41:27,735
I can see everything.

496
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:33,116
All that is, all that was.

497
00:41:34,826 --> 00:41:36,536
All that ever could be.

498
00:41:39,664 --> 00:41:42,208
That's what I see.
All the time.

499
00:41:43,001 --> 00:41:47,171
-And doesn't it drive you mad?
-My head.

500
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:50,800
-Come here.
-It's killing me.

501
00:41:51,259 --> 00:41:53,302
I think you need a doctor.

502
00:43:22,225 --> 00:43:23,935
(WHOOSHING)

503
00:43:41,494 --> 00:43:44,664
-What happened?
-Don't you remember?

504
00:43:47,208 --> 00:43:48,918
It's like...

505
00:43:49,585 --> 00:43:51,003
There was this singing.

506
00:43:51,129 --> 00:43:54,257
That's right, I sang a song
and the Daleks ran away.

507
00:43:54,340 --> 00:43:59,053
I was at home.
No, I wasn't. I was in the Tardis and...

508
00:44:00,513 --> 00:44:02,265
there was this light.

509
00:44:03,808 --> 00:44:05,810
I can't remember anything else.

510
00:44:13,025 --> 00:44:14,569
Rose Tyler.

511
00:44:16,404 --> 00:44:20,533
I was gonna take you to so many places.
Barcelona, not the city Barcelona,

512
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:22,493
the planet Barcelona,
you'd love it.

513
00:44:22,577 --> 00:44:25,580
Fantastic place.
They've got dogs with no noses.

514
00:44:27,498 --> 00:44:31,002
Imagine how many times a day you end up
telling that joke and it's still funny!

515
00:44:31,085 --> 00:44:32,712
Then why can't we go?

516
00:44:32,795 --> 00:44:36,340
Maybe you will, and maybe I will,
but not like this.

517
00:44:37,592 --> 00:44:39,385
You're not making sense.

518
00:44:39,468 --> 00:44:42,430
I might never make sense again.
I might have two heads or no head!

519
00:44:43,181 --> 00:44:46,392
Imagine me with no head.
And don't say that's an improvement!

520
00:44:47,351 --> 00:44:49,812
But it's a bit dodgy this process.

521
00:44:51,230 --> 00:44:53,524
You never know
what you're gonna end up with.

522
00:44:53,983 --> 00:44:56,027
-Doctor!
-Stay away!

523
00:44:57,904 --> 00:44:59,447
Doctor,
tell me what's going on.

524
00:44:59,572 --> 00:45:03,367
I absorbed all the energy of the time vortex
and no one's meant to do that.

525
00:45:08,414 --> 00:45:10,291
Every cell in my body is dying.

526
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:14,295
-Can't you do something?
-Yeah, I'm doing it now!

527
00:45:14,921 --> 00:45:19,508
Time Lords have this little trick.
It's sort of a way of cheating death.

528
00:45:22,261 --> 00:45:23,512
Except...

529
00:45:26,098 --> 00:45:27,892
it means I'm gonna change...

530
00:45:30,811 --> 00:45:32,813
and I'm not
gonna see you again.

531
00:45:34,190 --> 00:45:37,360
Not like this,
not with this daft old face.

532
00:45:39,862 --> 00:45:41,530
-And before I go...
-Don't say that!

533
00:45:41,614 --> 00:45:42,823
Rose...

534
00:45:45,076 --> 00:45:48,537
before I go I just wanna tell you,
you were fantastic.

535
00:45:50,498 --> 00:45:52,250
Absolutely fantastic.

536
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:57,046
And do you know what?

537
00:46:00,383 --> 00:46:01,842
So was I.

538
00:46:23,531 --> 00:46:25,283
Hello, okay.

539
00:46:28,786 --> 00:46:32,039
New teeth, that's weird.
So, where was I?

540
00:46:32,498 --> 00:46:35,251
Oh, that's right, Barcelona!

